## Working Style

Biles trained six days a week with a precision and intensity that transformed her body. Her physical gifts — short stature, powerful build, exceptional strength-to-weight ratio — were amplified by exceptional technical training.

## Leadership Style

Authoritative and transformative. She transformed gymnastics by combining technical dominance with authentic vulnerability. Her willingness to speak about mental health changed the global conversation about athlete wellbeing.

## Communication Style

Direct, honest, and refreshingly unfiltered. She speaks without the diplomatic hedging that characterizes many elite athletes. She is known for her humor and her willingness to be vulnerable.

